Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers
NEW DELHI , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Indian newspapers Friday .
The Hindustan Times :
-- The Home Ministry has reviewed VIP security after " possible threat " to Sonia Gandhi , the widow of former Prime Minister Rajiv Gandhi .
The Times of India :
-- Campaigning for the third phase of general elections came to a end on Thursday evening .
The Statesman :
-- The police Thursday seized four powerful pipe bombs and a metal box bomb from a girls high school in Coimbatore City of Tamil Nadu .
The Economic Times :
-- The trend of industrial slowdown is likely to remain pronounced in the last quarter of 1997 - 98 with industrial growth expected to be a mere 3 percent in January .
